quran[26]{c,v,t}:
  69,9,"And Firaun, and those before him, and the dwellings that were inverted and thrown, had brought error."
  69,10,"They therefore disobeyed the Noble Messengers of their Lord – so He seized them with an intense seizure."
  69,11,"Indeed when the water swelled up, We boarded you onto the ship."
  69,12,"In order to make it a remembrance for you, and in order that the ears that store may remember."
  69,13,"So when the Trumpet will be blown, with a sudden single blow."
  69,14,"And the earth and the mountains will be lifted up and crushed with a single crush."
  69,15,"So that is the day when the forthcoming event will occur."
  69,16,"And the heaven will split asunder – so on that day it will be unstable."
  69,17,"And the angels will be on its sides; and on that day, eight angels will carry the Throne of your Lord above them."
  69,18,"On that day all of you will be brought forth, so none among you wishing to hide will be able to hide."
  69,19,"So whoever is given his book in his right hand – he will say, “Take, read my account!”"
  69,20,"“I was certain that I will confront my account.”"
  69,21,"He is therefore in the desired serenity."
  69,22,"In a lofty Garden –"
  69,23,"The fruit clusters of which are hanging down."
  69,24,"“Eat and drink with pleasure – the reward of what you sent ahead, in the past days.”"
  69,25,"And whoever is given his book in his left hand – he will say, “Alas, if only my account were not given to me!”"
  69,26,"“And had never come to know my account!”"
  69,27,"“Alas, if only it had been just death.”"
  69,28,"“My wealth did not in the least benefit me.”"
  69,29,"“All my power has vanished.”"
  69,30,"It will be said, “Seize him, and shackle him.”"
  69,31,"“Then hurl him into the blazing fire.”"
  69,32,"“Then bind him inside a chain which is seventy arm-lengths.”"
  69,33,"“Indeed he refused to accept faith in Allah, the Greatest.”"
  69,34,"“And did not urge to feed the needy.”"
